This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with the analysis of news articles and the writing styles employed by news producers. It also uses natural language processing techniques to compute content-based features. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) because it analyzes social media engagement features. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another likely sub-category because the paper deals with the discovery of news narratives and news attribution. 

Cybersecurity (cs.CY) is a possible sub-category because the paper includes maliciously fake news sources. 

Finally, Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) is another possible sub-category because the paper deals with the challenge of studying news producers in a complex media landscape.
